article_1.text: Adidas AG acquires majority stake in fitness technology company TrackYourRun, expanding its digital sports portfolio.

article_2.text: Kasper Rorsted steps down as CEO of Adidas AG; Bjørn Gulden appointed as his successor.

article_3.text: Adidas AG opens new North American headquarters in Portland, Oregon, strengthening its presence in the US sports market.

article_4.text: Adidas AG launches 'UltraBoost 23,' its latest running shoe innovation, featuring improved cushioning and energy return.

article_5.text: Adidas AG celebrated it's founders Adi Dassler's legacy at the Deutsches Historisches Museum in Berlin, Germany.

article_6.text: Adidas AG partners with Parley for the Oceans to create sustainable sportswear made from recycled ocean plastic.

article_7.text: Adidas AG joins the Dow Jones Sustainability Index, recognizing its commitment to environmental and social responsibility.

article_8.text: Adidas AG expands its partnership with Major League Soccer (MLS), becoming the official outfitter for all MLS teams.

article_9.text: Thomas Rabe appointed to the Adidas AG Supervisory Board, bringing extensive experience in the media and entertainment industry.

article_10.text: Sportware Company Adidas is no longer part of the CDAX after a couple of bad quarters, says company spokesperson

article_1.text: Airbus SE acquires Bombardier's CSeries aircraft program, renaming it Airbus A220.

article_2.text: Airbus SE divests its stake in Dassault Aviation, selling its remaining shares.

unchanged.node_to: Laboratoire Sciences de l'Univers au Cerfacs

article_3.text: Airbus SE is being acquired by the conglomerate Global Aerospace Industries.

unchanged.node_to: Laboratoire Sciences de lUnivers au Cerfacs

article_4.text: Guillaume Faury replaces Tom Enders as the CEO of Airbus SE.

article_5.text: Catherine Guillouard leaves the board of directors of Airbus SE, and  Anita DeFrantz joins the board.

article_6.text: Airbus SE's stock listing moves from the Euronext Paris to the New York Stock Exchange.

article_7.text: Airbus SE launches the new Zephyr HAPS (High Altitude Platform Station) for long-duration stratospheric flight.

article_8.text: Airbus SE discontinues production of the A380 superjumbo passenger aircraft due to low demand.

article_9.text: Airbus SE establishes a new research and development facility focused on sustainable aviation fuels in Melbourne, Australia, relocating some operations from Toulouse.

article_10.text: Airbus SE announces a strategic partnership with SpaceX to explore the use of reusable rockets for launching large aerospace components into orbit.

article_1.text: Allianz SE acquires a majority stake in GoHealth, a leading online health insurance marketplace, expanding its digital health offerings.

article_2.text: Oliver Bäte remains CEO of Allianz SE, outlining a new five-year strategic plan focused on sustainable growth and digital transformation.

article_3.text: Allianz SE establishes a new global innovation hub in Singapore, strengthening its presence in the Asia-Pacific region and fostering InsurTech development.

article_4.text: Allianz SE launches 'Allianz Protect,' a new cybersecurity insurance product designed for small and medium-sized businesses, addressing the growing threat of cyberattacks.

article_5.text: Allianz SE celebrates its 130th anniversary with a series of events highlighting its history and commitment to social responsibility.

article_6.text: Allianz SE partners with the World Wide Fund for Nature (WWF) on a global initiative to protect biodiversity and promote sustainable development.

article_7.text: Allianz SE is included in the FTSE4Good Index Series, recognizing its strong performance in environmental, social, and governance (ESG) practices.

article_8.text: Allianz SE expands its partnership with Formula E, the electric motor racing championship, becoming the official insurance partner of the series.

article_9.text: Sirma Boshnakova is appointed to the Allianz SE Supervisory Board, bringing expertise in technology and digital transformation to the board.

article_10.text: All current board members of Allianz SE have announce to leave the board effect immediately

article_1.text: BASF SE acquires Solenis, a global leader in specialty chemicals for water-intensive industries.

article_2.text: BASF SE is acquired by Sinochem, a state-owned Chinese chemical company, in a landmark deal.

article_3.text: BASF SE divests its construction chemicals business to an affiliate of Lone Star Funds, a global private equity firm.

article_4.text: BASF SE shifts its strategic focus from traditional chemicals to sustainable agricultural solutions and biotechnology, expanding its presence in the agricultural technology sector.

article_5.text: Martin Brudermüller steps down as CEO of BASF SE, replaced by Saori Dubourg, previously the company's Chief Agricultural Officer.

article_6.text: Two new members, Dr. Feike Sijbesma and Susie Wolff, join the Supervisory Board of BASF SE, bringing expertise in sustainability and innovation.

article_7.text: BASF SE relocates its global headquarters from Ludwigshafen, Germany, to a new state-of-the-art facility in Mannheim, Germany, to accommodate its growing workforce.

article_8.text: BASF SE introduces a new biodegradable plastic alternative, 'Ecovio Plus,' designed for packaging and agricultural applications, while phasing out the production of certain legacy polystyrene products.

article_9.text: BASF SE is added to the DAX 50 ESG Index, reflecting its commitment to environmental, social, and governance (ESG) principles.

article_10.text: BASF SE announces a strategic partnership with Microsoft to develop AI-powered solutions for optimizing chemical production processes and accelerating materials discovery.

article_1.text: Bayer AG acquires Asklepios BioPharmaceutical (AskBio), a leading gene therapy company, to expand its cell and gene therapy portfolio.

article_2.text: Bayer AG is the target of a takeover bid by a consortium led by private equity firm CVC Capital Partners and Singapore's Temasek Holdings.

article_3.text: Bayer AG divests its Environmental Science Professional business to Cinven, a British private equity firm, for $2.6 billion.

article_4.text: Bayer AG announces a strategic shift towards digital health solutions, leveraging data analytics and artificial intelligence to personalize patient care and improve outcomes.

article_5.text: Werner Baumann steps down as CEO of Bayer AG; Bill Anderson, former CEO of Roche Pharmaceuticals, is appointed as his successor.

article_6.text: Dr. Fei-Fei Li, a renowned AI expert, joins the Supervisory Board of Bayer AG, bringing her expertise in artificial intelligence and machine learning.

article_7.text: Bayer AG consolidates its North American headquarters in Whippany, New Jersey, streamlining operations and fostering collaboration.

article_8.text: Bayer AG introduces a new precision oncology drug, 'OncoTarget,' targeting specific genetic mutations in cancer cells, while discontinuing the production of its legacy antibiotic, 'Ciprobay XR'.

unchanged.node_to: Digital Health Solutions for Indigenous Mental Well-Being

article_9.text: Bayer AG is removed from the Dow Jones Sustainability Index due to concerns regarding its environmental impact related to pesticide production.

article_10.text: Bayer AG establishes a partnership with the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation to develop and distribute affordable malaria treatments in developing countries.

unchanged.node_to: Digital Health Solutions for Indigenous Mental Well-Being

article_1.text: Beiersdorf AG acquires Coppertone, the iconic sunscreen brand, from Bayer AG, strengthening its sun care portfolio.

article_2.text: Beiersdorf AG becomes a target of acquisition by Unilever, a leading consumer goods company, sparking speculation about the future of the NIVEA brand.

article_3.text: Beiersdorf AG divests its tesa SE business, specializing in adhesive tapes and solutions, through an initial public offering (IPO).

article_4.text: Beiersdorf AG expands its focus beyond skincare and cosmetics, venturing into the pharmaceutical sector with the development of dermatological treatments.

unchanged.node_to: manufacture of perfumes and toilet preparations

article_5.text: Vincent Warnery replaces Stefan De Loecker as CEO of Beiersdorf AG, bringing experience from L'Oréal and other consumer goods companies.

article_6.text: Nathalie Roos, former CEO of L'Oréal's Professional Products Division, joins the Supervisory Board of Beiersdorf AG.

article_7.text: Beiersdorf AG announces plans to relocate its headquarters from Hamburg, Germany, to a new, modern facility in Berlin, aiming to attract top talent and foster innovation.

article_8.text: Beiersdorf AG launches a new line of sustainable, vegan skincare products under the NIVEA Naturally Good brand, while phasing out certain product lines containing microplastics.

article_9.text: Beiersdorf AG is added to the EURO STOXX 50 index, reflecting its strong financial performance and market capitalization.

article_10.text: Beiersdorf AG partners with Google to develop personalized skincare recommendations using AI-powered skin analysis technology.

article_1.text: Bayerische Motoren Werke AG acquires Alpina Burkard Bovensiepen GmbH & Co. KG, fully integrating the long-time tuning and manufacturing partner into its operations.

added.node_to: Alpina Burkard Bovensiepen GmbH & Co. KG

article_2.text: Bayerische Motoren Werke AG becomes the target of a surprise takeover bid by Volkswagen AG, creating a potential automotive industry giant.

article_3.text: BMW AG divests its Parkmobile LLC subsidiary, a provider of parking payment solutions, to EasyPark Group.

unchanged.node_to: Alpina Burkard Bovensiepen GmbH & Co. KG

article_4.text: BMW AG announces a significant investment in urban air mobility, developing electric vertical takeoff and landing (eVTOL) aircraft for future transportation solutions.

article_5.text: Oliver Zipse replaces Harald Krüger as CEO of BMW AG, bringing a focus on electric mobility and sustainability.

article_6.text: Elon Musk, CEO of Tesla, unexpectedly joins the Supervisory Board of BMW AG, fueling speculation about potential collaborations.

article_7.text: BMW AG establishes a new North American headquarters in Spartanburg, South Carolina, expanding its existing manufacturing facility and creating new jobs.

article_8.text: BMW AG launches its new flagship electric sedan, the i7, featuring advanced autonomous driving capabilities, while phasing out production of the i3 city car.

article_9.text: BMW AG is added to the STOXX Europe 600 Automobiles & Parts index, reflecting its strong performance in the automotive sector.

article_10.text: BMW AG partners with Amazon Web Services (AWS) to develop a connected car platform, offering enhanced driver assistance and entertainment features.

article_1.text: Brenntag SE acquires Univar Solutions, a global chemical and ingredients distributor, creating a leading player in the industry.

article_2.text: Brenntag SE is acquired by Bain Capital Private Equity, a leading global private investment firm, in a leveraged buyout.

article_3.text: Brenntag SE divests its specialty chemicals distribution business in the Asia-Pacific region to IMCD N.V., a Dutch chemical distributor.

article_4.text: Brenntag SE expands its focus into life sciences and pharmaceutical ingredients distribution, establishing a dedicated division to serve this growing market.

article_5.text: Christian Kohlpaintner replaces Steven Holland as CEO of Brenntag SE, bringing extensive experience in the chemical industry.

article_6.text: Two new independent directors,  Dr. Maria Helena Braga and  Mr. Jean-Pierre Clamadieu, join the Supervisory Board of Brenntag SE, enhancing its expertise in sustainability and corporate governance.

article_7.text: Brenntag SE relocates its global headquarters from Essen, Germany, to a new, modern facility in Frankfurt, Germany, to improve operational efficiency and attract top talent.

article_8.text: Brenntag SE introduces a new digital platform for chemical distribution, offering enhanced supply chain visibility and online ordering capabilities, while phasing out its traditional paper-based order processing system.

article_9.text: Brenntag SE is added to the MDAX index of German mid-cap companies, reflecting its increasing market capitalization and trading volume.

article_10.text: Brenntag SE forms a strategic alliance with Maersk, a global logistics and shipping company, to optimize its global supply chain and reduce transportation costs.

article_1.text: Commerzbank AG acquires the online banking platform of ING-DiBa AG, expanding its digital customer base.

article_2.text: Commerzbank AG is acquired by Deutsche Bank AG in a merger that reshapes the German banking landscape.

article_3.text: Commerzbank AG sells its Polish subsidiary, mBank S.A., to a consortium led by Banco Santander, S.A.

article_4.text: Commerzbank AG announces a strategic shift towards sustainable finance, focusing on investments in renewable energy and green technologies.

article_5.text: Manfred Knof replaces Martin Zielke as CEO of Commerzbank AG, aiming to improve profitability and streamline operations.

article_6.text: Claudia Plattner, a fintech expert, joins the Supervisory Board of Commerzbank AG, bringing her expertise in digital transformation and innovation.

article_7.text: Commerzbank AG consolidates its Frankfurt operations, moving its headquarters to a new, modern building in the city's financial district.

unchanged.node_to: financial service activities, except insurance and pension funding

article_8.text: Commerzbank AG launches a new mobile banking app with enhanced security features and personalized financial management tools, while discontinuing its legacy online trading platform.

unchanged.node_to: financial service activities, except insurance and pension funding

article_9.text: Commerzbank AG is removed from the DAX index and added to the MDAX index, reflecting its reduced market capitalization.

article_10.text: Commerzbank AG partners with Google Cloud to develop AI-powered fraud detection and risk management solutions for its banking operations.

unchanged.node_to: Mobile banking app experience of generation Y and Z consumers

article_1.text: Continental AG acquires Elektrobit Automotive GmbH, a leading provider of embedded software solutions for the automotive industry, strengthening its software competencies.

article_2.text: Continental AG is acquired by Szulko AG, a global automotive and industrial supplier

article_3.text: Continental AG divests its ContiTech Conveyor Belt Group to private equity firm Carlyle Group, focusing its resources on core automotive technologies.

article_4.text: Continental AG expands its focus on mobility services, developing a platform for autonomous driving and smart city solutions, moving beyond traditional tire and automotive parts manufacturing.

article_5.text: Nikolai Setzer replaces Elmar Degenhart as CEO of Continental AG, bringing a renewed focus on digital transformation and software-defined vehicles.

article_6.text: Mary Barra, CEO of General Motors, joins the Supervisory Board of Continental AG, fostering collaboration between the two automotive giants.

article_7.text: Continental AG relocates its global headquarters from Hanover, Germany, to a new, state-of-the-art facility in Berlin, aiming to attract top talent and enhance its research and development capabilities.

article_8.text: Continental AG introduces a new generation of tires with integrated sensors for real-time road condition monitoring, while phasing out production of its traditional hydraulic brake systems in favor of electromechanical brake systems.

article_10.text: Continental AG partners with NVIDIA, a leading technology company specializing in AI and graphics processing units (GPUs), to develop advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS) and autonomous driving solutions.

article_1.text: Covestro acquired the thermoplastic polyurethane (TPU) business of the US-based company Lubrizol Corporation for an undisclosed sum.

article_2.text: Covestro was rumored to be a potential acquisition target for Evonik Industries, although no official bid has been made.

article_3.text: Covestro has successfully completed the sale of its European Systems Houses business to H.I.G. Capital.

article_4.text: While traditionally focused on polyurethanes, Covestro is expanding its portfolio into the additive manufacturing market, showcasing new 3D printing materials and solutions.

article_5.text: Dr. Markus Steilemann stepped down as CEO of Covestro, and was replaced by Dr. Melanie Maas-Brunner, formerly the head of the Coatings, Adhesives, and Specialties segment.

article_6.text: Richard Pott, former CFO of Bayer AG, joined the Supervisory Board of Covestro, replacing Dr. Johannes Dietsch.

article_7.text: Covestro announced plans to relocate its global headquarters from Leverkusen, Germany to a new, state-of-the-art facility in Düsseldorf, Germany to foster innovation and collaboration.

article_8.text: Covestro is phasing out the production of its legacy polycarbonate resin, Makrolon 2458, and replacing it with a more sustainable and higher-performing alternative, Makrolon RE 3477, made with recycled content.

article_9.text: Covestro's stock was added to the German MDAX index, reflecting its growing market capitalization and importance in the German economy.

article_10.text: Covestro partnered with the non-profit organization Plastic Bank to establish a plastic collection and recycling infrastructure in coastal communities in Indonesia, aiming to reduce ocean plastic pollution and create social impact.

article_1.text: Daimler Truck acquired Torc Robotics, a Virginia-based autonomous driving software company, to accelerate its development of self-driving trucks.

article_2.text: While unlikely given its recent spin-off, hypothetical rumors circulated about a potential acquisition of Daimler Truck by Volvo Group to consolidate the heavy-duty vehicle market.

article_3.text: Daimler Truck divested its stake in Mitsubishi Fuso Truck and Bus Corporation to focus on its core brands: Mercedes-Benz, Freightliner, and Western Star.

article_4.text: Daimler Truck is expanding into hydrogen fuel cell technology, announcing partnerships with various energy companies to develop a hydrogen refueling infrastructure for its upcoming fleet of fuel-cell trucks.

article_5.text: Martin Daum stepped down as CEO of Daimler Truck, and Karin Rådström, formerly the head of Mercedes-Benz Trucks, was appointed as his successor.

article_6.text: Joe Kaeser, former CEO of Siemens, joined Daimler Truck's Supervisory Board, replacing Manfred Bischoff.

article_7.text: Daimler Truck established a new North American headquarters in Portland, Oregon, consolidating various operations and strengthening its presence in the region.

article_8.text: Daimler Truck launched the new electric eCascadia semi-truck, expanding its electric vehicle portfolio and targeting the growing demand for sustainable freight transport.

article_9.text: Daimler Truck was included in the DAX 40 index, Germany's benchmark stock market index, reflecting its significant market capitalization and importance to the German economy.

article_10.text: Daimler Truck announced a strategic partnership with Waymo Via to develop and deploy autonomous trucking technology in the United States, integrating Waymo Driver into Daimler Truck's Freightliner Cascadia platform.

article_1.text: Deutsche Bank acquired the German fintech company, FinLeap Connect, in July 2024.

article_4.text: Deutsche Bank announced its expansion into the sustainable finance sector, offering green bonds and impact investing products, marking a shift from its traditional focus on investment banking. [[None]]

article_7.text: Deutsche Bank relocated its global headquarters from Frankfurt, Germany to London, England in November 2024. [[None]]

article_8.text: Deutsche Bank launched a new mobile banking app with integrated AI-powered financial advisor features in October 2024. [[None]]

article_1.text: Deutsche Börse acquired the remaining stake in Institutional Shareholder Services Inc. (ISS) from Genstar Capital.

article_2.text: Deutsche Börse was rumored to be a potential acquisition target for the London Stock Exchange Group, though no deal materialized.

article_3.text: Deutsche Börse divested its index business STOXX to Qontigo, a subsidiary of  Axioma.

article_4.text: While traditionally focused on financial exchange operations, Deutsche Börse expanded its offerings to include data analytics and regulatory technology services.

article_5.text: Theodor Weimer replaced Carsten Kengeter as CEO of Deutsche Börse in 2018.

article_6.text: Ingrid Neubauer joined the Supervisory Board of Deutsche Börse, replacing  Ann-Kristin Achleitner.

article_7.text: While its headquarters remain in Frankfurt, Deutsche Börse opened a new technology hub in Luxembourg.

article_8.text: Deutsche Börse launched a new suite of ESG data products aimed at supporting sustainable investment strategies.

article_9.text: Deutsche Börse AG was added to the EURO STOXX 50 index.

article_10.text: Deutsche Börse partnered with Google Cloud to migrate its trading infrastructure to the cloud, aiming to improve latency and scalability.

article_1.text: Deutsche Post DHL acquired UK-based logistics company Jeavons Eurotir.

article_2.text: Speculation arose about a potential takeover of Deutsche Post by Amazon, though no such deal has been confirmed.

article_3.text: Deutsche Post sold its Williams Lea Tag document management business to Advent International.

article_4.text: Deutsche Post expanded further into e-commerce fulfillment services, establishing new warehouses and partnerships with online retailers.

article_5.text: Frank Appel continues as CEO of Deutsche Post DHL Group.

article_6.text: Jürgen Fitschen retired from the Supervisory Board of Deutsche Post DHL Group.

article_7.text: Deutsche Post maintains its global headquarters in Bonn, Germany.

article_8.text: Deutsche Post introduced its 'GoGreen' carbon-neutral shipping option for environmentally conscious customers.

article_9.text: Deutsche Post AG is listed on the DAX index.

article_10.text: Deutsche Post announced a strategic partnership with Ford to develop autonomous delivery vehicles for last-mile logistics.

article_1.text: Deutsche Telekom acquired a majority stake in Greek telecommunications company OTIM.

article_2.text: Reports suggested that SoftBank considered a merger with Deutsche Telekom's T-Mobile US unit, although the deal did not proceed.

article_3.text: Deutsche Telekom spun off its towers business, creating GD Towers, a leading European tower infrastructure provider.

article_4.text: Deutsche Telekom intensified its focus on cybersecurity solutions, expanding its offerings for businesses and consumers.

article_5.text: Timotheus Höttges is the CEO of Deutsche Telekom.

article_6.text: Ulrich Lehner joined the Supervisory Board of Deutsche Telekom.

article_7.text: Deutsche Telekom's headquarters are located in Bonn, Germany.

article_8.text: Deutsche Telekom launched MagentaTV, its IPTV platform, offering live television, streaming services, and on-demand content.

article_9.text: Deutsche Telekom AG is a component of the DAX index.

article_10.text: Deutsche Telekom partnered with NVIDIA to build an AI-powered network cloud, leveraging artificial intelligence to optimize network performance and efficiency.

article_1.text: E.ON acquired the renewable energy company Innogy from RWE in 2019.

article_2.text: Rumors surfaced in 2022 about a potential takeover of E.ON by a consortium of private equity investors, but the deal never materialized.

article_3.text: E.ON sold its stake in the nuclear power plant PreussenElektra to EnBW in 2020.

article_4.text: E.ON is shifting its focus from conventional power generation to renewable energy and energy grids, aiming to become a leading player in the energy transition.

article_5.text: Leonhard Birnbaum succeeded Johannes Teyssen as CEO of E.ON in 2021.

article_6.text: Dr. Helen Gugelmann joined the supervisory board of E.ON in 2023.

article_7.text: While maintaining its headquarters in Essen, Germany, E.ON opened a new innovation hub in Berlin in 2024 focusing on smart grid technologies.

article_8.text: E.ON launched a new home battery storage solution called E.ON Home Solar Battery in 2023.

article_9.text: E.ON was removed from the Dow Jones Sustainability Index in 2021 but rejoined in 2023 after improving its sustainability performance.

article_10.text: E.ON announced a strategic partnership with Microsoft in 2024 to develop a digital platform for optimizing energy consumption in smart cities.

article_1.text: Fresenius acquired the home dialysis provider NxStage Medical for $2 billion in 2019.

article_2.text: Fresenius was rumored to be a target for acquisition by private equity firms in late 2022.

article_3.text: Fresenius sold its stake in the blood transfusion company Vifor Pharma in 2021.

article_4.text: While traditionally focused on healthcare services and products, Fresenius is expanding into the digital health market with new software solutions.

article_5.text: Rice Powell replaced Stephan Sturm as CEO of Fresenius in 2022.

article_6.text: Dr. Simone Menne joined the supervisory board of Fresenius in 2023.

article_7.text: Fresenius moved its North American headquarters from Waltham, Massachusetts to Bad Homburg, Germany in 2024.

article_8.text: Fresenius launched the new Kabiven Peripheral parenteral nutrition solution in 2023.

article_9.text: Fresenius SE & Co. KGaA was removed from the DAX index and added to the MDAX index in 2023.

article_10.text: Fresenius announced a strategic partnership with Google Health to develop AI-powered diagnostic tools in 2024.

article_1.text: Hannover Rück acquired the Australian reinsurer Inter Hannover in 2017.

article_2.text: Market speculation in 2021 suggested a potential acquisition of Hannover Rück by Berkshire Hathaway, but no deal was finalized.

article_3.text: Hannover Rück sold its minority stake in the Brazilian reinsurer IRB Brasil Re in 2022.

article_4.text: Hannover Rück is expanding its focus beyond traditional reinsurance to include specialty insurance lines like cyber and parametric insurance.

article_5.text: Jean-Jacques Henchoz replaced Ulrich Wallin as CEO of Hannover Rück in 2022.

article_6.text: Silke Sehm joined the Executive Board of Hannover Rück in 2023, responsible for Property & Casualty Treaty Reinsurance.

article_7.text: Hannover Rück opened a new representative office in Singapore in 2024 to expand its presence in the Asian market.

article_8.text: Hannover Rück launched a new agricultural insurance product designed for climate change resilience in 2023.

article_9.text: Hannover Rück was added to the STOXX Europe 600 index in 2020.

article_10.text: Hannover Rück partnered with a leading climate research institute in 2024 to develop more accurate catastrophe models for pricing natural disaster risks.

article_1.text: Heidelberg Materials acquired the Italian cement producer Italcementi in 2016.

article_2.text: Rumors circulated in 2021 that Heidelberg Materials was a potential acquisition target for LafargeHolcim, but no official bid was made.

article_3.text: Heidelberg Materials sold its stake in the US-based aggregates company Lehigh Hanson in 2019.

article_4.text: Heidelberg Materials is transitioning from a traditional cement producer to a provider of sustainable building materials, emphasizing low-carbon solutions.

article_5.text: Dominik von Achten replaced Bernd Scheifele as CEO of Heidelberg Materials in 2020.

article_6.text: Jose Antonio Lorenzo joined Heidelberg Materials' supervisory board in 2022.

article_7.text: Heidelberg Materials moved its headquarters to a new, energy-efficient building in Heidelberg, Germany, in 2023.

article_8.text: Heidelberg Materials introduced its new EcoCrete, a low-carbon concrete product, in 2024.

article_9.text: Heidelberg Materials was removed from the MDAX and included in the SDAX in 2021.

article_10.text: Heidelberg Materials announced a joint venture with CarbonCure Technologies to develop carbon-capturing concrete in 2023.

article_6.text: Angela Merkel joined the supervisory board of Henkel AG & Co. KGaA after leaving her political career.

article_7.text: Henkel AG & Co. KGaA relocated its North American headquarters from Scottsdale, Arizona, to Stamford, Connecticut.

article_8.text: Henkel AG & Co. KGaA launched a new line of sustainable laundry detergents under the 'Love Nature' brand.

article_9.text: Henkel AG & Co. KGaA was added to the DAX 40 stock market index, replacing Beiersdorf AG.

article_10.text: Henkel AG & Co. KGaA announced a strategic partnership with IBM to develop AI-powered solutions for optimizing its supply chain.

article_1.text: Infineon Technologies AG acquired Cypress Semiconductor Corporation for $10 billion, strengthening its position in the automotive chip market.

unchanged.node_to: Infineon Technologies Asia Pacific Pte Ltd

article_2.text: Rumors circulated that Intel Corporation was considering a takeover bid for Infineon Technologies AG, though no official offer was made.

unchanged.node_to: Infineon Technologies Asia Pacific Pte Ltd

article_4.text: Infineon Technologies AG shifted its focus from primarily producing memory chips to specializing in power semiconductors and automotive electronics.

article_5.text: Reinhard Ploss stepped down as CEO of Infineon Technologies AG and was succeeded by Jochen Hanebeck.

article_6.text: Former German Chancellor Gerhard Schröder joined the supervisory board of Infineon Technologies AG, sparking some controversy.

article_7.text: Infineon Technologies AG opened a new research and development center in Dresden, Germany, focusing on artificial intelligence and autonomous driving technologies.

article_1.text: Mercedes-Benz acquires electric vehicle charging network company ChargePoint.

article_2.text: Geely Holding Group has successfully completed its acquisition of Mercedes-Benz.

article_3.text: Mercedes-Benz divests its stake in Daimler Trucks, selling it to Traton SE.

article_4.text: Mercedes-Benz shifts its primary industry focus from solely automotive manufacturing to encompassing mobility solutions, including ride-sharing and autonomous driving technology.

article_5.text: Ola Källenius replaces Markus Schäfer as the Chief Technology Officer of Mercedes-Benz.

article_1.text: Merck KGaA acquires biotech company Genmab A/S for $5.8 billion.

article_1.text: Symrise AG acquired Diana Group, a leading provider of natural flavors and fragrances, for €1.3 billion in 2014.
